PREAMBLE

The Government of the Republic of South Africa, herein represented by the Minister of

Justice and Correctional Services ofthe Republic of South Africa, hereinafter referred to as "the South African side";

AND

The Minister for Europe and Foreign Affairs ofthe French Republic, hereinafter referred to as "the French side";

CONSIDERING the Agreement on Trade, Cooperation and Development between the

European Community and its Member States, on the one hand, and the Republic of South

Africa, on the other hand, the Agreement between the Government of the French Republic and the Government of the Republic of South Africa on Police Cooperation, signed on 26

June 1998, as well as the excellent relations existing between the two countries and the need to promote cooperation and sustainable development in their countries;

DETERMINED to strengthen understanding, friendship and solidarity between the two countries;

GUIDED by the desire to develop and encourage cooperation between the two countries in all areas ofmutual interest;

HAVE AGREED as follows:

ARTICLES

JOINT CONTRIBUTIONS OF THE PARTIES

In addition to the individual contributions of the Participants described in Articles 6 and 7, the Parties shall :

(a) undertake to ensure the success ofthe training programme and to make all reasonable efforts to ensure the proper execution ofthe programme;

(b) co-operate on all matters related to this Cooperation Protocol with the utmost care, diligence, skill, efficiency and economy;

(c) respect the principles and practices of project management;

(d) communicate to each other, in good time and free ofcharge, all available information and data which may be necessary for the proper execution ofthe programme, insofar as this information or data is in the care or control ofthe Party who communicate it;

(e) undertake any other responsibility agreed upon between them; and (f) jointly ensure the quality and monitoring of the programme where appropriate and share the use ofresources in accordance with the terms ofthis Cooperation Protocol

ARTICLE 6

CONTRffiUTIONS OF THE SIU

The SID shall undertake the following responsibilities, in addition to the collective responsibilities outlined in this Cooperation Protocol:

(a) facilitate and coordinate the development and implementation of the DARWIN training programme;

(b) assume the costs of logistical arrangements for its staff, including transport, training venue and catering;

(c) establish training lists and dates of the implementation schedule and communicate them to the French technical expert;

(d) manage, communicate and record all information related to the DARWIN training program;

(e) establish an internal evaluation system for Participants to ensure that they meet the training requirements;

(f) manage the implementation of an agreed project plan for the deployment of the

DARWIN real-time forensic training programme;

