ARTICLE 7

CONTRIBUTIONS OF THE FRENCH EMBASSY

(1) The Embassy shall :

(a) provide a technical expert to the SIU, responsible for developing the training material for the DARWIN training programme;

(b) ensure that the technical expert empowers SIU trainers to use the DARWIN tool to enable them to implement its deployment;

(c) finance the travel of the French expert trainer to the SIU provincial offices during the implementation of the programme for quality control purposes;

(d)

ensure that the French expert trainer in Cyber Forensics submits periodic reports to the French Embassy and the SIU on the implementation of the programme;

(e) provide the SIU, free of charge, with all available information and data that maybe necessary for the exercise of its responsibilities under this Cooperation Protocol or that may strengthen the capacity of the SIU.

(2) The Embassy shall, through the technical expert- (a) advise and guide the development of the study programmes;

