(b) be responsible for monitoring the quality ofeach training session in order to improve its effectiveness and provide support to the trainers;

(c) receive feedback sent by the SIU Training and Development Department on behalfof the beneficiaries ofthe training;

(d) Use the evaluations to improve the programme following the training provided to the pilot training group, if necessary, in partnership with the Sill Training and

Development Department and retrain the trainers ifnecessary;

(e) provide remote monitoring of the trainer during the delivery of training at the SIU regional training centres and shall carry out "face-to-face" monitoring in exceptional circumstances, as required;

(f) describe the training programme and how it is shared with the Sill Training and

Development Department;

(g) provide assistance to build the capacity ofSIU trainers responsible for the deployment ofthe DARWIN training programme;

(h) provide the SIU with an overall assessment in order to select additional trainers from among its members, ifnecessary;

(i) facilitate the provision ofa French expert in online training to enhance the capacity of

SIU trainers; and (j) carry out a feasibility study on a regional platform that would allow training to be delivered in one location.

ARTICLE 8

FINANCIAL PROVISIONS

(1) This programme shall be developed with the assistance ofthe French Embassy.

(2) The SIU shall be responsible for financing the logistical arrangements ofits staff

(3) The French Embassy shall be responsible for the placement ofa technical expert at the

SIU for the duration of its contract with the Ministry of Europe and Foreign Affairs, for the development of the "DARWIN" training programme, the monitoring and quality control ofthe programme, and the provision ofan online training expert.

(4) Contributions under this Cooperation Protocol are within the limits of the Parties' annual resources, in particular their budgetary availability and current operating allocations.

